==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acclaim
<hw>Ac*claim"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>acclamare</ets>; <ets>ad</ets> + <ets>clamare</ets> to cry out. See
<er>Claim</er>, <er>Clamor</er>.]</ety> <mark>[R.]</mark> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To applaud.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A glad <xex>acclaiming</xex> train.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To declare by acclamations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>While the shouting crowd⟦br⟧
<qex>Acclaims</qex> thee king of traitors.</q>
<rj><qau>Smollett.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To shout; <as>as, to <ex>acclaim</ex> my
joy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acclaim</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Acclaim
<hw>Ac*claim"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To shout applause.</def>⟦br⟧
